cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about image deconvolution using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a Recurrent Gradient Descent Network (RGDN) that incorporates deep neural networks into a fully parameterized gradient descent scheme. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on synthetic benchmarks and real-world images, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
